Pantheon Music Engine v0.1

Goal: turn any prompt, scene, story, doctrine, or emotional arc into a strong music brief in any chosen style.

Core principle

Music generation becomes:

meaning extraction → emotional geometry → structural translation → style rendering

Not:
	•	“write a random song about X”

But:
	•	“convert the inner shape of X into sound”

⸻

1. Input types

The engine should accept:
	•	one sentence
	•	a paragraph
	•	a story
	•	a dialogue
	•	a doctrine / manifesto
	•	an image description
	•	a mythic archetype
	•	a scene objective

Example inputs:
	•	“A knight holds the gate knowing he will die.”
	•	“Turn this breakup story into an early-2000s pop anthem.”
	•	“Make Pantheon sound like cyber-gospel trap.”
	•	“Convert this military memoir excerpt into cinematic post-rock.”

⸻

2. Hidden extraction layer

From the prompt, extract:

Narrative arc
	•	rise
	•	fall
	•	tension
	•	release
	•	reversal
	•	triumph
	•	ambiguity

Emotional blend
	•	grief
	•	awe
	•	rage
	•	discipline
	•	longing
	•	holiness
	•	seduction
	•	menace
	•	play

Energy profile
	•	low / medium / high
	•	constant vs pulsed
	•	smooth vs jagged

Mythic posture
	•	guardian
	•	pilgrim
	•	conqueror
	•	witness
	•	exile
	•	prophet
	•	trickster
	•	revenant

These become the latent control values.

⸻

3. Music translation layer

Map extracted values into music variables.

Meaning → music
	•	discipline → tight rhythm, restrained dynamics
	•	awe → open intervals, wide pads, choirs
	•	rage → distortion, dense percussion, fast attack
	•	holiness → reverb space, suspended chords, choral texture
	•	longing → melodic lift, unresolved tones
	•	menace → low drones, sparse pulse, dissonance
	•	triumph → upward contour, stronger cadence, fuller mix

Arc → arrangement
	•	tension → build
	•	revelation → drop or harmonic bloom
	•	collapse → strip instrumentation
	•	resolve → simplify and center

⸻

4. Style shell

After the meaning skeleton is built, apply the requested style:
	•	trap
	•	country
	•	cinematic
	•	metal
	•	synthwave
	•	gospel
	•	EDM
	•	folk
	•	drill
	•	orchestral
	•	indie
	•	dark ambient
	•	hyperpop

Important rule:

style is the clothing, meaning is the body

So the same story can be rendered as:
	•	cinematic score
	•	radio pop
	•	black metal
	•	worship music
	•	club anthem

while still preserving the same inner geometry.

⸻

5. Output template

The engine should output:

A. Title

A strong title from the core meaning

B. Style brief

Genre, era, production flavor

C. Emotional profile

2–5 dominant emotional vectors

D. Structure

Intro / verse / pre / chorus / bridge / outro
or
ambient build / impact / decay

E. Sonic palette

Instruments, texture, rhythm, vocal type

F. Hook concept

The central musical/emotional payoff

G. Optional lyrics seed

A few lines or chorus ideas

